#Topic Canvas
#Class SkCanvas

Canvas defines how the output of drawing is represented, and how it is clipped and transformed.

Canvas encapsulates the state to draw into Surface.
Canvas has a reference to Surface, and a stack of Canvas_Matrix and Canvas_Clip values.
Each draw call transforms the geometry of the object by the concatenation of all Canvas_Matrix
values in the stack. 
The transformed geometry is clipped by the intersection of all of Canvas_Clip values in the stack.

Canvas holds the state of the drawing device. The state the drawn object 
is held by Paint, provided as a parameter to each of the draw calls.
Paint holds attributes such as Paint_Color, Paint_Typeface, Paint_Text_Size, Stroke_Width, Paint_Shader and so on.

Surface has several implementations, including: Raster_Surface, GPU_Surface, PDF_Surface, and SVG_Surface.

Canvas backed by Raster_Surface draws to memory visible to the CPU. 
Canvas backed by GPU_Surface uses Vulcan or OpenGL to draw to the GPU.
Canvas backed by PDF_Surface or SVG_Surface captures drawing commands.

Each Canvas has a specific type of Surface. Once Canvas is constructed, Surface_Type can't
be changed.

To draw with Canvas, create Surface of the appropriate type, then request its Canvas.  

#Subtopic Canvas_Constructors

Create the desired type of Surface to obtain its Canvas when possible. Canvas_Constructors are useful
when no Surface is required, and some helpers implicitly create Raster_Surface.

